Hi there! 

I'm seeking a like-minded woman to share a disasterous 3-9 month relationship with, ending in acrimony, emotional chaos, and possibly legal proceedings. 

I'm 30 year old white male, well educated, I hold down a good job and am pretty stable. I'm told I'm fairly good looking and I am in shape- you certainly won't be disappointed with me. I'm generally caring and very honest. I have no trouble carrying on a conversation and I love to laugh. I think I'm alot of fun (but who doesn't right?), I'm a little sarcastic and I can take it as good as I get it. I fit in anywhere, not because I change who I am, but because I'm easy to get along with. 

I am looking for an attractive female who will at first give me obsessive love, praise and devotion - but whose paranoia, self-loathing and fear of rejection and abandonment will eventually lead her to alternately push me away and pull me closer in a love/hate cycle that will lead to infidelity, consensual sexual violence, and the eventual emotional breakdown of one or other party - or if we're lucky - both! 

You should: 

* be 18 to 35 years old; 
* have a history of short, intense, drama-driven relationships;
* enjoy degrading and dehumanising sex;
* have undergone negative psychiatric evaluations in the past; and
* be willing to threaten self-harm and/or annihilation as a weapon to control your partner and make them stay with you and care for you.


Although not completely necessary, I would prefer women: 

* with a pretty smile (that makes me think you are sweet);
* who have a killer pair of legs; 
* who are married or perhaps already in unstable relationships;
* that drink to forget; and
* who have had a previous established diagnosis of Borderline or Dependent Personality Disorder or Bi-Polar Affective Disorder - or who are currently taking Lithium Carbonate, SSRIs, or Ativan 

If you think you meet these requirements (and wow, I'm getting excited just writing them!), please don't hesitate to get back to me as soon as possible. In the meantime, thank you for reading, and do take care. 

